organization.description:
At 1st April 2017 Blaby District Council employed 282 full-time equivalent members of staff.

The Council serves 42,000 households and a population of around 96,500.

Estimated gross expenditure for the year 2017/18 is approximately £31.6 million.

Services provided by the Council include refuse collection and recycling, street cleansing, public and environmental health, housing, parks and open spaces, leisure facilities, car parking, community safety, and housing and council tax benefits.

results.notes:
Available for England, Scotland and Wales  in a number of Ordnance Survey (OS) products: Open Names (bounding box and point geometry), MasterMap Topography Layer (point geometry), Vector Map Local (point geometry) and Vector Map District (point geometry). Small-scale cartographic representations are also available.Â  All data is collected by Ordnance Survey as part of their role as the National Mapping Agency of Great Britain. This data is often used for geocoding, service delivery and statistical analysis. 
          Keywords: Cities, Settlements, Geographical Names, Place Names
